# Cursor Hooks

Hooks run custom scripts before or after agent actions. Configured in `.cursor/hooks.json` (project root).

Reference: [Cursor Hooks Docs](https://cursor.com/docs/agent/hooks) · Contract: `.cursor/HOOKS.md`

## Hook events

| Event | When | Use case |
| ----- | ---- | -------- |
| `afterFileEdit` | After agent edits a file | Auto-format, lint, validate |
| `beforeShellExecution` | Before shell command runs | Block dangerous commands |
| `afterShellExecution` | After shell command completes | Audit logs, capture PR URLs |
| `stop` | Agent session ends | Final verification, cleanup |
| `sessionStart` | New conversation begins | Inject context, set env vars |
| `preToolUse` | Before any tool runs | Validate tool usage (with matcher) |
| `beforeReadFile` | Before agent reads a file | Redact secrets, access control |

## Current project hooks

### afterFileEdit

- **`bash/after-file-edit.sh`** (single hook, 22s timeout): Prettier + ESLint `--fix` when project has config; then warns on stderr if `console.log` appears in edited JS/TS.

### beforeShellExecution (with matcher)

- **`bash/before-shell-guard.sh`**: runs only when the shell command matches the configured pattern — blocks destructive `rm`, broad deletes on Windows, destructive `git` commands, force-push to main/master; asks before `--no-verify`, other force pushes, and force-kills.

### afterShellExecution (with matcher)

- **`bash/after-shell-pr.sh`**: runs only when the command matches `gh pr create` — logs PR URL and review hint.

### stop

- **`bash/stop-console-audit.sh`** (12s timeout): logs agent `status` from stdin when present; audits git-changed JS/TS for leftover `console.log`.

### Not enabled in `hooks.json`

- **`preToolUse` prompt hooks**: not used — they steal focus from chat on every edit. Prefer linters and review.

## Git pre-commit vs Cursor hooks

Cursor **does not expose a native Git pre-commit event** for its model hooks. Prompt hooks run inside the agent/tool lifecycle, not inside Husky or Git itself.

- If the goal is **Cursor-native model review**, `preToolUse` is the right place — but prompt-type hooks are intentionally not enabled here (UX).
- If the goal is **true Git pre-commit review for every commit**, that requires an external CLI or API call from Husky. Cursor's built-in prompt hooks cannot be called from `.husky/pre-commit`.

## Real Git pre-commit

This repo also uses a real Git hook:

- **Versioned hook**: `.githooks/pre-commit`
- **Local activator**: `.git/hooks/pre-commit` delegates to the versioned script without editing `core.hooksPath`
- **Checks**: `.cursor/scripts/pre-commit-checks.mjs`

Current deterministic checks:

- Parse staged `.json` files to fail fast on invalid JSON
- Run `sh -n` on staged `.sh` files when `sh` is available
- If `.cursor/hooks.json` or files under `.cursor/hooks/` are staged, verify that `hooks.json` only references existing hook scripts

## Pipeline overview

```text
Agent edits file
  └── [afterFileEdit] after-file-edit.sh: format + console.log warn (one subprocess)

Agent runs shell command
  ├── [beforeShellExecution] Guard (matcher: risky commands only)
  └── [afterShellExecution] PR logger (matcher: gh pr create only)

Agent session ends
  └── [stop] stop-console-audit.sh: status line + console.log audit

Git commit starts
  └── [.githooks/pre-commit] staged-file deterministic checks
```

## Exit codes (per Cursor docs)

- `0` = success / allow
- `2` = deny (block the action)
- Other = hook failed, action continues (fail-open)

## Requirements

- **jq**: all scripts parse JSON input with it
- **npx**: used by lint hook
- **Git Bash or WSL** on Windows: scripts are bash
